&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As CHAOS Industries scales production of advanced defense systems, manufacturing execution becomes a critical competitive advantage. We are seeking a Chief of Staff, Manufacturing to serve as a force multiplier for our manufacturing organization—driving strategic initiatives, solving complex operational challenges, and ensuring critical priorities translate into measurable outcomes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working closely with Manufacturing Leadership, Supply Chain, Engineering, Quality, Finance, and Program Management, you will lead high-impact projects that improve throughput, enable scale, and strengthen operational performance across the business. This is a builder’s role: you will identify bottlenecks, develop solutions, and drive execution in areas that do not neatly fit within existing organizational boundaries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate combines the structured thinking and analytical rigor of a top-tier consulting background with the ownership mindset and bias for action required to build in a fast-paced manufacturing environment. This is a 0-to-1 role: you will be standing up structure, owning cross-functional work that has no home yet, and acting as connective tissue across a leadership team that is still being built—not optimizing a machine that already runs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;High performers in this role are positioned to move into manufacturing leadership seats as the organization scales.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establish and run the manufacturing operating rhythm—performance reviews, operating mechanisms, and decision forums that create accountability across functions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own cross-functional work that does not yet have a clear home: identify bottlenecks, run root-cause analyses, drive issues to closure, and stand up the structure to keep them closed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build executive-level analyses, business cases, and decision-support materials that inform strategic and operational decisions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop the metrics backbone—throughput, quality, labor, capacity, and on-time delivery reporting—into a single operating picture leadership can run on.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support capacity planning, facility expansion, and production ramp efforts as a hands-on project owner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead special, high-priority initiatives on behalf of manufacturing leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree and 7+ years of experience spanning both a strategy/consulting environment and an operating role where you owned execution and results (manufacturing, industrial, or operations).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience leading complex, cross-functional initiatives from problem definition through implementation.&lt;/li&gt;
