&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Role Overview:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CHAOS Industries builds advanced defense and national-security systems at the speed our customers need them—and contracts is where that speed is either enabled or lost. We are seeking an experienced Contracts Administrator to manage the full lifecycle of our government and commercial contracts, from proposal through closeout, with the rigor of a prime and the pace of a startup.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will partner with Program Management, Finance, Legal, and Supply Chain, you will be the system of record for contractual actions across the portfolio and a trusted business advisor on the requirements, deliverables, and risks that move our programs forward. This is a hands-on role working primarily across negotiated procurements under FAR Part 15 and commercial product and service acquisitions under FAR Part 12.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer assigned contracts, task orders, and modifications across their full lifecycle, ensuring every action is documented, compliant, and audit-ready.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain contract files, records, and data within CHAOS systems as the authoritative source for deliverables, funding, periods of performance, and key milestones.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and manage contractual deliverables, reporting deadlines, funding actions, and option exercises, flagging risks to Program Management before they become problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support solicitation review, proposal preparation, and award activities for both commercial-item (FAR Part 12) and negotiated (FAR Part 15) acquisitions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and process contract modifications, amendments, and change documentation, confirming consistency with the agreements reached.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain representations and certifications in SAM and assemble reps-and-certs packages for proposal submissions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate contract execution and signature workflows, and support compliance reviews, government audits, and contract closeout.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain customer correspondence and contractual communications, and assist with NDAs, teaming agreements, and consulting agreements as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help build the playbook—contribute to the templates, processes, and tools of a contracts function being stood up from the ground up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Requirements:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree and 8+ years of contract administration experience; or a Master&#39;s degree and 6+ years; or, in lieu of a degree, 12+ years of directly related experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience supporting U.S. Government acquisitions under FAR Part 12 (commercial products and services) and FAR Part 15 (contracting by negotiation).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with the DFARS, including its key clauses and contract flowdowns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated experience administering contract modifications and maintaining contract documentation and records of record.&lt;/li&gt;
